On 3/5/03 1:58 PM, "Richard Atwell" <ratwell(-at-)mac.com> wrote:

> Can someone tell me what the thread size on the tap on the 3/4 fuel rail for
> testing the fuel pressure? I know it's non standard and most gauges don9t
> fit.
> 
> --
> Richard
> 1978 Westfalia CDN
> Cupertino, CA

Richard,

Just attach a gauge with a piece of fuel line and clamps. I learned this
from jamie rivers, who pointed out that the tap in the fuel rail has a
nipple shape to it, so it is designed to be used this way. I believe the
thread on the screw plug is m5, not sure on the pitch.

Scott Lyons
